Tucson listens to Rodimus and Legacy but as always he was going to prepare a
reason for his actions, and before he can even speak, the inevitable
happens.  He falls to one knee and then to the other.  The battery fluid
loss had indeed taken him.

Quickstride and Uproar are quick to try and catch him.

&quot;Woahh, Rodimus and Legacy have a point Sir.  It&#39;s time you took care of
your own needs.&quot;

Replies Quickstride as he and Uproar now help him to his feet.  Tucson still
had that apprehension.  Although he needed help, he still felt that the
needs of his comrades had to come first.

&quot; My - own needs - can wait.  The - others need help more than I do.&quot;

Straight Shot could see what was happening.

&quot;Stubborn as usual.  C&#39;mon Tucson, Rodimus and Legacy are right, you need ta
take care of yourself! I know what happened in the past was hard for you ta
take, but that wasn&#39;t your fault!  You got struck from behind by Cyclonus,
and there was no way of predicting that!&quot;

Tucson sighs.

&quot;I - could have prevented it though.  And I - can&#39;t - let it happen again.&quot;

Straight Shot could see that Tucson did need help urgently.

&quot;Legacy, please get Tucson ta the CR Chambers ASAP.  And make sure he
actually takes your advice.&quot;

Tucson couldn&#39;t say anything else.  He knew his little sister was right.

Straight Shot looks to Rodimus now knowing why Tucson was acting as he was.
It wasn&#39;t out of revenge, it was out of compassion, and guilt.  But a guilt
he did not deserve to carry.

&quot; He feels really bad about what happened..  He thinks that your
disappearence and abduction was his fault.  In all truths it was no one&#39;s
fault but Hydras&#39;s.  Before he became a Prime, he really took his job
seriously and still does but back then, for an Autobot, he was all
dedication and didn&#39;t care what kind of consequences he&#39;d face while going
above and beyond the call of duty.  All he cares about is his comrades, and
even back then, his loyalty was soley for you and the others.  He was always
so proud to be working with you, and would do anything to uphold the level
of heroism that&#39;s always expected of Autobot and Maximal kind.  Then, that
day, the time you were taken from us..  That was the day he was trying to
divert enemy attentions away from you by doing what was highly
uncharacteristic of himself.  Decoy work was always deemed for those who
were natural built speedsters, but he&#39;s no speedster.  When he chose his
form, he chose the working class vehicle, which is known more for strength
and durability than speed. But out of desperation to try and save you, he
did what he normally didn&#39;t do, and then, that&#39;s when he got shot by
Cyclonus. It took him off line instantly.  He doesn&#39;t remember anything
after that.  I was taken off line at the same time, but, I did stay
conscious enough to see the blast. Shortly after he went off line, I did.
But strange, I remember more than he does.  And that&#39;s why he&#39;s acting as he
is.  He&#39;s trying to sorta make up for lost time.&quot;

